definitions.definition: the condition of being considered more important than someone or something else; priority in importance, order, or rank.
examples: his desire for power soon took precedence over any other consideration
synonyms: eminence More"quarrels over precedence"take priority over
come before "the children's needs take precedence over all the other concerns"

definitions.definition: the order to be ceremonially observed by people of different rank, according to an acknowledged or legally determined system.
examples: quarrels over precedence among the Bonaparte family marred the coronation
